{
  "stem": "13096.6",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Every night after that, until, you know, we moved away, he will come for half an hour to hear just my Spanish-- my Spanish song, which was 'Caminito.' And then, in reward, to reward me there in the camp, he will give me double ration of food, which the food consisted with the Russian, kasha in the morning with a little bit of sugar.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Kasha is wheat, boiled wheat.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "That, it was breakfast.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Lunchtime, the same kasha with salt and haricot beans.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And at night, kasha and haricot beans.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Day in, day out, day in, day out.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They say that, in Russia, everybody eats the same.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But it was not true, because we saw the officer.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They were eating meat fricadelles, and chops, and this and that.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But the soldier and us, we was kasha.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Kasha is the main, like you say, the macaroni for the Italians.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my reward for singing at night for the general was to have double kasha for lunch, for breakfast, and for dinner, which I was sharing with my friends there, with me.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because even that we were know they giving enough portion, but it was still, you know, not enough.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were just sharing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then, we were staying in that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they move us to another camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Another camp, it was I think Bialyk itself.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Bialyk and Bialystok, they are nearly more or less nearby.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There, we stay, you know, like two months, two months in the other thing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were taking us, the girls, to go and clean the-- the places where the Russians were, you know, to clean the floor like servants, you know.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then we didn't like that, because if we were free, why we have to go there and clean those places?",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
